} }; const getGenderedUsers = async () => { try { const response = await axios.get("http://localhost:8000/gendered-users"); console.log(response); setGenderedUsers([response.data]); } catch (error) { console.log(error); } }; console.log("gendred users", genderedUsers); useEffect(() => { getUser(); }, []); useEffect(() => { if (user) { getGenderedUsers(); } }, [user]); const updateMatches = async (matchedUserId) => { try { await axios.put("http://localhost:8000/addmatch", { userId, matchedUserId, });
